# 🏗️ Implementation Plan — Riverpod + Notification System

## Overview

This plan integrates **Riverpod** as the global state management solution across the entire app and builds a **dual notification system** (Local + FCM).

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Riverpod Providers"
        A[authProvider] --> B[Auth State: LoggedIn/Guest]
        C[timelineProvider] --> D[Cached Timeline Events]
        E[favoritesProvider] --> F[Heart Icons Everywhere]
        G[lastVisitedProvider] --> H[Resume Reading Card]
        I[chatStreamProvider] --> J[ChatGPT-style Typing]
    end

    subgraph "Notification System"
        K[Local Notifications] --> L[24h Inactivity Reminder]
        M[FCM Push] --> N[Ramadan / Islamic Events]
    end

    H --> K
    B --> A
```

---

## Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Both Local + FCM will be used.** They serve different purposes:
> | Feature | Technology | Why |
> |---|---|---|
> | "Resume Reading" 24h reminder | **Local Notification** | Works offline, no server needed, privacy-first |
> | 🕌 Ramadan reminders, 📅 Islamic event announcements | **FCM Push** | Server-initiated, reaches all users at once |

> [!NOTE]
> **Riverpod Version:** We will use `flutter_riverpod` (latest stable). This uses `ProviderScope` at the root and `ConsumerWidget` / `ConsumerStatefulWidget` in screens.

